Foot and mouth disease, Israel
------------------------------
Information received on 28 Apr 2011 from Dr Michel Bellaiche,
Director, Veterinary Services and Animal Health, Ministry of
Agriculture and Rural Development, Beit Dagan, Israel


Summary
Report type Immediate notification
Start date 17 Apr 2011
Date of 1st confirmation of the event 27 Apr 2011
Report date 28 Apr 2011
Date submitted to OIE 28 Apr 2011
Reason for notification Reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence 27 Mar 2011
Manifestation of disease Clinical disease
Causal agent Foot and mouth disease virus
Serotype O
Nature of diagnosis Suspicion, Clinical, Laboratory (basic),
Laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country

New outbreaks
Outbreak 1 (Yavne'El) Yavne'El, Kineret, Hazafon
Date of start of the outbreak 21 Apr 2011
Outbreak status Continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit Village
Species Cattle
Susceptible 70
Cases 6
Deaths 0
Destroyed 0
Slaughtered 0
Affected Population Beef cattle. 6 cows with salivation and
limping.

Outbreak 2 (Senir) Senir, Tsefat, Hazafon
Date of start of the outbreak 17 Apr 2011
Outbreak status Continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit Village
Species Cattle
Susceptible 700
Cases 35
Deaths 0
Destroyed 0
Slaughtered 0
Affected Population The animals are fattening calves 9-12 months
old.
The lesions were severe ulcers in gums and tongue, salivation and
limping.

Summary of outbreaks Total outbreaks: 2
Total animals affected
Species Cattle
Susceptible 770
Cases 41
Deaths 0
Destroyed 0
Slaughtered 0

Epidemiology - Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection.
Unknown or inconclusive

Control measures - Measures applied. Quarantine; Movement control
inside the country; Zoning; Vaccination in response to the
outbreak(s); * No treatment of affected animals

Measures to be applied - Screening; Disinfection of infected
premises/establishment(s)

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type Kimron Veterinary Institute (National
laboratory)
Species Cattle
Test enzyme-linked immunosorbent assay (ELISA)
Test date 27 Apr 2011
Result Positive

Species Cattle
Test polymerase chain reaction (PCR)
Test date 27 Apr 2011
Result Positive

Species Cattle
Test virus isolation
Test date 28 Apr 2011
Result Positive

Future Reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

